Package blf.blockchains.hyperledger.instructions

Class HyperledgerLogEntryFilterInstruction

  • java.lang.Object
    • blf.blockchains.hyperledger.instructions.HyperledgerLogEntryFilterInstruction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Instruction
    public class HyperledgerLogEntryFilterInstruction
extends Object
implements Instruction
    HyperledgerLogEntryFilterInstruction is an Instruction for the Hyperledger log extraction mode of the Blockchain Logging Framework. It extracts the requested event from the current Block and stores the extracted parameter values in the ProgramState.

      • parseChaincodeEvent

        private void parseChaincodeEvent​(HyperledgerProgramState hyperledgerProgramState,
                                 org.hyperledger.fabric.sdk.ChaincodeEvent ce)
        Tries to parse the ChaincodeEvent in the manner the manifest requested.

        Firstly, it tries to parse the payload as a JSON string. If that fails, it tries to extract a single parameter from the unstructured payload.

        Parameters:
        hyperledgerProgramState - The current ProgramState of the BLF.
        ce - The current ChaincodeEvent to analyze.

      • parseNestedJsonPayload

        private void parseNestedJsonPayload​(HyperledgerProgramState hyperledgerProgramState,
                                    org.hyperledger.fabric.sdk.ChaincodeEvent ce,
                                    org.json.JSONObject obj)
        Tries to parse an event from a nested JSON object, if another JSON object is contained in the top-level JSON object of the payload and its key is the requested event name. If such object is not found, the top-level JSON object is tried to be handles as a flat JSON object containing the event parameters.
        Parameters:
        hyperledgerProgramState - The current ProgramState of the BLF.
        ce - The ChaincodeEvent to analyze.
        obj - The top-level JSON object that was successfully parsed from the event payload.

      • parseNonStructuredPayload

        private void parseNonStructuredPayload​(HyperledgerProgramState hyperledgerProgramState,
                                       org.hyperledger.fabric.sdk.ChaincodeEvent ce,
                                       String payloadString,
                                       org.json.JSONException jsonException)
        Tries to parse a single parameter from an unstructured payload.

        If the event payload does not contain structured JSON data, we can not now if it holds any other structure of multiple parameters internally, as all we see is an array of bytes. We can try to parse one single parameter out of these bytes.

        Parameters:
        hyperledgerProgramState - The current ProgramState of the BLF.
        ce - The ChaincodeEvent to analyze.
        payloadString - The payload of the ce, already converted to a string.
        jsonException - The exception thrown by the JSON parser, the reason why the JSON could not be recognized.
